title: Lonely Planet - Discover Florida - 1st Ed (2012).epub Gooner
description:
Lonely Planet - Discover Florida (Travel Guide) - 1st Edition (2012).epub Gooner

Publisher: Lonely Planet; 1 edition (March 1, 2012)
Language: English
ISBN-10: 1742204902
ISBN-13: 978-1742204901

Lonely Planet: The world's leading travel guide publisher

Lonely Planet Discover Florida is your passport to all the most relevant and up-to-date advice on what to see, what to skip, and what hidden discoveries await you. Fish the Florida Keys, hit up a hot Miami club for all-night dancing, or kayak by cypress domes and mangroves in the Everglades; all with your trusted travel companion. Discover the best of Florida and begin your journey now!

Inside Lonely Planet Discover Florida:

* Full-color maps and images throughout

* Highlights and itineraries show you the simplest way to tailor your trip to your own personal needs and interests

* Insider tips save you time and money and help you get around like a local, avoiding crowds and trouble spots

* Essential info at your fingertips - including hours of operation, phone numbers, websites, transit tips, and prices

* Honest reviews for all budgets - including eating, sleeping, sight-seeing, going out, shopping, and hidden gems that most guidebooks miss

* Cultural insights give you a richer and more rewarding travel experience - including history, art, literature, cinema, music, architecture, landscapes, wildlife, beaches, food, drink, and more

* Over 25 color local maps

* Useful features - including Month-by-Month (annual festival calendar), Travel with Kids, and What's New

* Coverage of Walt Disney World, Orlando, Universal Studios, SeaWorld, Tampa Bay, Gulf Coast, Palm Beach, Gold Coast, The Everglades, Miami, the Keys, and more

The Perfect Choice: Lonely Planet Discover Florida, our easy-to-use guide, is perfect for travelers who seek the most popular attractions a destination has to offer. Filled with inspiring and colorful photos, this guide focuses on the best of the best.

* Looking for a comprehensive guide that recommends a wide range of experiences, both popular and offbeat, and extensively covers all the state has to offer? Check out Lonely Planet's Florida guide.

* Looking for a guide focused on Miami and the Keys? Check out Lonely Planet's Miami & the Keys guide for a comprehensive look at all region has to offer.
Authors: Written and researched by Lonely Planet, Adam Karlin, Jeff Campbell, Jennifer Denniston, and Emily Matchar.

About Lonely Planet: Started in 1973, Lonely Planet has become the world's leading travel guide publisher with guidebooks to every destination on the planet, as well as an award-winning website, a suite of mobile and digital travel products, and a dedicated traveler community. Lonely Planet's mission is to enable curious travelers to experience the world and to truly get to the heart of the places they find themselves in
